# Testing strategy (clean architecture)

The classic pyramid (~50–60% unit, ~25–30% integration, ~10–15% e2e) is a **maturity baremo**, not a sprint quota. Choose the test type from the **layer** you change. Full detail: `docs/architecture/testing-strategy.md` and `docs/architecture/adr-004-testing-by-architecture-layer.md`.

## Layer → test type

| Layer | Typical paths | Required test |
|-------|---------------|---------------|
| **Domain** | `core/domain`, `core/scoring`, pure `features/*/utils` or `models`, domain Zod | **Unit** (`*.spec.ts`) — required for new/touched rules |
| **Use case** | `features/*/services`, orchestration hooks/policies | **Integration** (`*.integration.spec.ts`) — real modules + in-memory/fake ports |
| **Adapter** | `core/api`, `core/storage`, HTTP↔domain mappers | **Contract** (`*.contract.spec.ts`) — ~**100%** of the public port/surface you touch |
| **UI journey** | critical product flows | **E2E** (`e2e/*.spec.ts`) — few, high-value only |

## Do

- Prefer fixing behavior with the **lowest** useful layer (domain unit before e2e).
- Fake ports at the boundary in integration tests; do not hit real network or device storage.
- When touching an adapter, assert Zod/DTO shapes, error mapping, and port fulfillment.
- Keep e2e for risky journeys (learn/profile, catalog filters, ranking, compare, calculator, legal).
- Climb toward the baremo **incrementally** in each PR — add missing integration/contracts; do not delete useful domain units to “fix” percentages.

## Do not

- Do not call a single pure-function spec an “integration” test.
- Do not mock the domain under test in its own unit test.
- Do not add trivial UI render snapshots without a business or contract assertion.
- Do not require e2e for every component change.
- Do not skip adapter contract tests without an explicit PR note (e.g. pure rename).

## PR checklist (when code changes)

- [ ] Domain touched → unit covers the rule (+ edge/warning if relevant)
- [ ] Use case touched → integration with fakes
- [ ] Adapter touched → contract for the public API changed
- [ ] Critical journey touched → e2e considered / updated if needed

## Commands

- `pnpm run test:unit` — `src/**/*.spec.ts` (include `*.integration.spec.ts` / `*.contract.spec.ts` in the same CI path)
- `pnpm run test:e2e` — Playwright
- `pnpm run test:ci` — full quality gate before done
